united has reported to the faa airlines are required to submit 
certain information about failures but sometimes submit more data 
than is required so that the information can be used by others in 
the aviation industry 
the last engine flameout reported was in september 1984 when an 
engine quit with 5500 pounds of fuel in a tank and the aft boost 
light on the report said the problem could not be duplicated in 
subsequent tests 
in november 1980 an engine flamed out at 33500 feet when the 
drive shaft failed the faa records do not indicate how repairs 
were made 
