including a july 1988 incident in which the crew reported the left 
gear red light was on with the gear handle up some landing gear 
position indicator parts had to be replaced the report said 
in january 1987 the flight crew reported it had no indication 
that the landing gear was locked down but the jet landed without 
incident maintenance crews found the landing gear handle sticking 
and lubricated the handle the system checked out after that the 
faa report shows 
in june 1987 a right gear door cable was replaced after the 
right main gear showed both a green and red light 
