troopers in 15 east coast states issued hundreds 
of traffic citations and seized stolen car parts but made few drug 
arrests in a crackdown along interstate 95 one of the nations 
busiest drug trafficking corridors 
in the 24hour sweep that ended at 8 am today a jacksonville 
fla man was jailed on drug trafficking charges and virginia state 
troopers seized 140 pounds of marijuana from one traveler 
arrest totals were still being compiled said chuck peltier a 
spokesman for the washington dcbased international association 
of chiefs of police 
the effort was called operation coflame representing 
cooperation among agencies from florida to maine 
