new orleans and was hospitalized at that time he was brought back 
to philadelphia and underwent surgery to stop internal bleeding he 
retired in 1988 
he was born in 1910 in cleveland to polish immigrant parents and 
was ordained in 1937 
described as the only american who ever was mentioned as a 
