four to eight hours before the july 13 crash 
rahman based the opinion on the extent of peritonitis an 
infection that can be caused by a ruptured intestine 
root who claims he passed out at the controls and rode on 
autopilot for nearly four hours until the singleengine cessna ran 
out of fuel has not been able to explain how he received the 
bullet wound 
i do not believe that the peritonitis that i observed 
could have developed in less than two hours and most likely has 
been present for somewhat longer say four to eight hours rahman 
wrote in a report to the national transportation safety board 
which is investigating the incident 
