this was a very very radical departure from any kind of 
fiction film anybody was making in the country ferrer said 
noting its documentary style and controversial topic it was a 
picture which broke a tremendous number of shibboleths and it 
established a new freedom in making films 
albert jr said de rochemont deliberately picked unknown white 
actors ferrer and the late beatrice pearson who had been in only 
one film before lost boundaries and who abandoned her career a 
short time later 
though some critics film buffs and historians have criticized 
the movie for casting whites in the lead roles as was done in 
other movies at that time such as show boat and pinky the 
film did feature a few black actors including canada lee and leigh 
whipper 
the movie also has been criticized for creating an unbelievable 
premise that the couple are forced to leave their black community 
because other blacks reject their whiteness at that time well 
before the slogan of black is beautiful permeated society fair 
skin was more acceptable in the black community than dark skin 
keene and gorham were fictionalized as the single keenham 
character names were changed the family became the carters and 
the family reduced to two children in the film directed by alfred 
l werker but most incidents were authentic albert jr said 
lost boundaries fell into obscurity when the company that 
owned it film classics folded its catalog was sold to warner 
bros the chance of rereleasing or televising it now is slim 
because its unclear who owns the distribution rights the movie 
had been shown on television years ago 
i think its the best picture i was ever in as an actor 
said the 71yearold ferrer in a telephone interview from his home 
outside santa barbara calif i still feel that way i 
thought it was a great opportunity for all of us 
ferrer who went on to become a producer and director felt 
strongly enough about the story to go against the advice of his 
booking agency and make his screen debut in the film the move 
could have destroyed his career but all of us had a certain real 
conviction about the theme of the picture and the content of the 
picture and i didnt hesitate 
the johnston family was and is proud that their story was used 
to promote racial understanding said albert jr a 63yearold 
retired department store buyer and composer 
we thought it was quite a historical first and that it 
contributed immensely to the thinking of society he said 
