as lawyers and legislators choose sides on flag measures not 
many are saying that the best thing to do is nothing the issue is 
so flammable that just about everybody wants action or thinks it 
inevitable 
thats the point behind borks banter at a house hearing the 
other day the question has become whether to ban flag desecration 
by act of congress or by amendment to the constitution rather 
than whether it is necessary or desirable to do either 
one exception charles fried another conservative scholar and 
