u s west on friday reported lower net income in 
the second quarter due to a onetime gain in the yearago period 
but noted that its nontelephone operations continue to grow 
for the period ended june 30 u s west reported earnings of 
2586 million or 142 a share down 23 percent from net income 
of 3363 million or 183 a share a year ago 
excluding last years onetime aftertax gain of 887 million 
from the sale of its 19 percent interest in u s west newvector 
group u s west said net income rose 44 percent 
total revenue for the quarter totaled 24 billion up 4 percent 
from 23 billion for the comparable period last year 
although a little more than 90 percent of u s west revenues come 
from its telephone operations it also owns companies involved in 
real estate financial services computer software cellular 
telephones and other businesses 
our 1989 earnings were right where we expected them to be 
said u s west chief executive jack mcallister in a statement our 
growth in earnings per share continues to come from our 
nontelephone operations and we dont expect that to change 
for the six months net income totaled 5082 million or 278 
a share on revenues of 483 billion compared with profit of 
5768 million or 313 a share on revenues of 444 billion 
