henley group inc said friday it has agreed 
to purchase the shares of fisher scientific group inc it does not 
already own for about 144 million 
henley which agreed to pay 2225 a share already owns about 
81 percent of fisher stock until 1987 fisher had operated as a 
wholly owned henley subsidiary and will return to that status said 
spokesman norman ritter 
last month henley offered 2050 a share for the fisher stock 
but several stockholders challenged the price in a lawsuit the 
higher price reached after negotiations is subject to court 
approval 
based in pittsburgh fisher makes and distributes laboratory and 
medical products henley also is involved in the manufacture of 
aircraft equipment the production of methanol and real estate 
henley had said it was interested in the fisher stock purchase 
as a way to facilitate the possible sale of fishers 
instrumentation laboratory in lexington mass and imed in san 
diego 
but ritter said henley is going to reconsider all of its 
options with respect to all the fisher businesses he declined to 
elaborate 
