hopes for lower interest rates faded friday in 
the credit markets as traders reassessed remarks made a day earlier 
by federal reserve chairman alan greenspan 
the pessimism pushed bond prices down the treasurys benchmark 
30year bond was off 932 point or 281 per 1000 in face 
amount the yield which rises when the price falls edged up to 
815 percent from 813 percent late thursday 
greenspan said thursday in a midyear report to congress the fed 
had shifted its top priority to avoiding a deep recession from 
fighting inflation bond prices rallied after the remarks but then 
receded late thursday and on into friday 
by the time we heard the entire testimony it became clear that 
the fed doesnt have all the evidence it wants to cut interest 
rates right away said fred n peck president and chief economist 
of hillcrest economics group in new city ny 
cutting rates would stimulate economic growth but it could also 
lead to a resurgence of inflation 
a huge weekly increase in a broad measure of the nations money 
supply announced late thursday indicated there may already be 
plenty of money in the banking system to fuel economic growth 
if they ease at all theyre going to need a lot of evidence 
that the economy is slowing peck said 
in the secondary market for treasury securities prices of 
shortterm governments were down 132 point to 332 point 
intermediate maturities dropped 116 point to point and longterm 
issues declined 532 point to 1132 point according to telerate 
inc the financial information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer declined 141 to 118597 
in corporate trading industrials also posted declines moodys 
investment grade corporate bond index which measures total return 
on a portfolio of 80 corporate bonds with maturities of five years 
or longer fell 007 to 32939 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds fell 116 point to 94 1732 the average 
yield to maturity was 720 percent about even with late thursday 
yields on threemonth treasury bills increased to 837 percent 
as the discount rose 6 basis points to 810 percent yields on 
sixmonth bills rose to 821 percent as the discount rose 5 basis 
points to 779 percent yields on oneyear bills rose to 8 percent 
as the discount rose 2 basis points to 747 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks traded at 9 percent down from 9316 percent late thursday 
