a picture of that house hangs inside the front door of the 
companys current headquarters dubbed the taj mahal by 
kauffman 
kauffman worked 16 hours a day as marion grew quickly going 
public in 1965 that was all fun that was a lot of fun he 
said 
after a dry spell in the 1970s marions sales exploded in the 
late 1970s on the strength of the heart drug cardizem 
unlike many pharmaceutical companies marion doesnt do its own 
basic chemical research instead it licenses compounds from other 
companies develops them for medical use and sells them 
company officials project 1 billion in sales this year but 
analysts said those sales would dip in 1992 when other companies 
can begin making generic versions of cardizem 
